Evidaxis is multi-licensed by component. There is no single repo-wide license.

  Code (etl/, web/src/, web/scripts/, spine/*.py, tests/,
        collectors/, dead-man/, .github/, deploy scripts) .... Apache-2.0  -> LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt
  Data (data/, entities/, taxonomy/) ....................... CC0-1.0     -> LICENSE-data.md
  Methodology prose (/methodology) ........................ CC-BY-4.0   -> https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
  Fonts (web/public/fonts/) ............................... OFL-1.1     -> LICENSES/OFL-1.1.txt

See LICENSING.md for the authoritative map and rationale, REUSE.toml for the
machine-readable mapping, and NOTICE for the Apache-2.0 attribution.
